\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec3 Hi. In our earlier videos this week, we looked at ways data can conspire to mislead us. We looked at problems caused by bad measurement systems and biased selection mechanisms. These are data quality issues. They result in the data we're looking at giving a distorted picture of the reality we're trying to understand. We want to look at this, but the data is showing us this. Then we looked at the problems of confounding that restrict our ability to draw cause and effect conclusions from observational data. It simply can't be done reliably. What's common about all these problems is that none of them go away as we get more data. They're big data problems, as well as small data problems.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl260\sa326\partightenfactor0
{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://www.futurelearn.com/courses/data-to-insight/8/steps/508378#"}}{\fldrslt 
